The paper discusses methods for collecting swimmer data from videos, which involves computer vision techniques such as object detection and tracking. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning for swimmer detection and tracking, which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the collected swimming data, such as in sports analytics and human-computer interaction, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), respectively.
